The author, Nicholas Connor Priebe, discusses his experience as an intern at the Office of Presidential Correspondence and highlights President Trump's support for rural areas. Priebe, who comes from a small town on the Eastern Shore of Virginia, mentions the President's efforts to conserve Tangier Island and his invitation to local business owners to the White House as part of the Made in America initiative. Priebe expresses pride in the President's approach to addressing the concerns of Americans, particularly those from rural areas. He believes that President Trump's initiatives protect American industries, family businesses, and bring hope to citizens across the United States.